        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Collingwood was founded in 1959 after the area was annexed by the City of Calgary in 1910.</p>
            <p>The community had a populace of 2,222 people living in 978 homes in the 2012 municipal census, down -0.4% from its 2011 census of 2,231. In 2012, it had a total population of 1,390/km2 (3,600/sq. mi) on a total land of 1.6 km2 (0.62 sq. mi).</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 43.2 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Charleswood has an average of 2.4 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 50% female and male residents. A whopping 21% of the residents of Collingwood are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Collingwood's real estate is primarily comprised of detached single-family houses. They usually have beautiful views and are close to one of the neighbourhood parks or smaller green areas. There are many affluent properties here, but there are also low-rise condos. The majority of the population are families and students attending the nearby University of Calgary. Homeowners in Collingwood are known for sticking around and staying put year after year.</p>
            <p>It is an ideal place for investing in real estate due to its closeness to the university and other educational facilities.</p>
